<div class="copy-section">
<details>
<summary>How do I use this thing
</summary>
<p>
<br>
QR is an extension that uses STScript for ease of... doing things. Anything, really. To get an overview of what 'anything' entails, type in
</p>
<pre>
<code>
/help slash
</code>
</pre>
<p>
You can also check the ST page on STScript
<a href="https://docs.sillytavern.app/usage/st-script/">by clicking here.</a>
I will be giving an overview of what you should edit, and other useful shorthands though.
<br>
If you plan on using this (or QR's in general) for a longer time, please download this extension:
</p>
<pre>
<code>
https://github.com/IceFog72/SillyTavern-SimpleQRBarToggle
</code>
</pre>
<br>
<p>
It gives QR's the ability to be hidden with a simple button press rather than cluttering up the screen. 
<br>
<b>Warning:</b> This is meant to be customised to your tastes. Unfortunately, I cannot account for every edge case people want. You can ask me if you have questions, but you are mostly on your own here. This means you will spend a bit of time getting things sorted the way you want. It will, however, probably save you time in the long run and teach you a cool ST feature so YMMV. I did my best here to give instructions.
</p>
</details>

<details>
<summary>
How do I use this thing 2
</summary>
<p>
<b>First, you want to hide all the QR's you don't plan on using.</b>
<br>
You do this by going into the QR extension, clicking the three dots next to the entry you don't want, scrolling down, and setting it as 'Invisible'. Obviously auto-execute should be off (it's off by default). 
<br><b>Next, it's editing time.</b>
The Gem, DS, OAI and OpenRouter buttons are for quickswapping between models, including toggling the correct prompts. Hide/delete the ones you don't need, as always, then check the following:
<br>
1. If using a proxy, input the name of your proxy instead of 'default'. If you don't use a proxy/don't know what that is, delete the argument.
<br>
2. You can edit which model will be pulled up via the <code>/model</code> argument. Simply put in whatever name the api uses (e.g. gemini-flash-2.5, deepseek-chat, gpt-4.1, etc.).
<br>
3. For Gemini, I have the no think prompts on by default. All the prompts that are LLM specific are listed in the QR's, so toggle on/off whatever you want to use for a given model. It is as simple as replacing the "on" with "off" and vice-verse. There's also the "toggle" argument, which will toggle between off and on depending on the current status of the prompt.
<br>
4. DS isn't set up for chutes because I do not like DS on chutes very much. You'll need to set it up yourself via using the api argument to set it to whatever chutes uses.
<br>
5. If you don't like the little pop-ups, delete the <code>/echo</code> argument in its entirety.
<br>
<b>What if something I want toggled isn't there by default?</b>
<br>
Toggling a prompt uses the following argument:
<code>
/setpromptentry name="name" off/on/toggle
</code>
The name has to be the <b>full name, including emojis</b>. If you type this argument into the reply box, ST can search up the correct prompt. Off/on/toggle will have to be set yourself, obv.
<br>
6. <b>For Group chatters:</b>
You can control who replies via the argument:</p>
<pre>
<code>
/trigger Name
</code>
</pre>
<p>
Replace name with the name of your KZK. This will bring up a cool button in the QR section that will let only that character reply. Best to be used with replies set to Manual. You can also set this to only appear if you're in that Group Chat by assigning it to the group via the QR extension.
</p>
</details>

